<p>
The first thing you need to understand is the difference 
between degrees and radians. All numbers are radians, 
unless they have a degree symbol. 180deg = <img src="../../Functions/image35.png" alt="pi" style="height:12px;">. So, <img src="../../Functions/image36.png" alt="180/pi" style="height:16px;">. 
If you need to convert from one to the other, 
you can use that. to convert 30 degrees to radians, 
for example, multiply by pi/180deg. 
30deg*pi/180deg=30*pi/180 
(The degree sign cancels) =pi/6 . You can go back, too: 
pi/6*180deg/pi=180deg/6=30deg 
(The pi cancels). Also, when you are finding the sine or 
cosine or something of an angle, make sure your 
calculator is in degrees if your angle has a degree symbol. 
For everything else, make sure your calculator is in 
radians.</p>

